pr_review_comment_body:
@whimboo 

Maybe I misread your statement from the issue (link #215). I read it as: "Remove mac64 option"... so I did ;)

I did not give the option in the regex of to download either macosx or macosx64 because I thought this might lead to a bug or inaccuracies (not possible to download a specific build because of it...)

@texasaggie97 I don't know if 'direction' will be the way to go for this. If I remember this right, we use this exclusively (today) to name the context manager for Acquisition vs Generation. I don't think either applies to NI-SWITCH, and NI-HSDIO would also be problematic.

@Fladolcetta made do a simple scanning example, to illustrate what this would look like (separate PR).

If there's agreement, I can open an Issue and not hold this PR.

For `if` statements, the `{` should be on its own line.
```
if (...)
{
    ....
}
else
{
    ....
}
```
